WEBVTT

00:06.380 --> 00:08.996
[theme music playing]

00:28.520 --> 00:30.647
["Breaking Free" playing]

00:42.200 --> 00:44.156
[Clay] I'm still waiting for Hannah Baker.

00:44.250 --> 00:45.160
[man] Who?

00:45.250 --> 00:47.571
[Clay]
Slqe Miller. I'm here for Skye Miller.

00:50.590 --> 00:53.969
She's still in recovery.
They'll move her up here in a few hours.

00:54.670 --> 00:57.889
That's what the other nurse said
every hour for the past seven hours.

00:57.970 --> 01:00.677
Kid, go home. Come back in the morning.

01:00.970 --> 01:03.473
Will she be okay?
Look, I just need to know.

01:03.560 --> 01:05.881
Go home. Come back.

01:05.980 --> 01:08.221
Cause you're always there
All the time

01:08.310 --> 01:12.064
On every face I meet
On every road I drive

01:12.150 --> 01:13.981
You're not my savior

01:14.070 --> 01:18.234
Just someone I used to see

01:18.320 --> 01:23.997
I am broken
Something's wrong inside of me

01:24.080 --> 01:26.241
I feel violent

01:26.330 --> 01:27.820
[Clay] I'm still waiting for Hannah Baker.

01:27.920 --> 01:29.740
-[echoing] Hannah Baker...
- Like I'm dying

01:29.920 --> 01:35.415
I feel broken
Maybe I'm just breaking free

01:38.640 --> 01:40.130
[car rewing]

01:43.640 --> 01:44.766
[tires screeching]

01:45.180 --> 01:46.169
[grunts]

01:57.650 --> 01:58.696
[Clay breathing heavily]

02:06.290 --> 02:08.076
[grunting]

02:08.540 --> 02:12.169
Clay, it's five o'clock in the morning.
What the hell is going on?

02:12.460 --> 02:15.588
Slqe is my girlfriend.
But we haven't had sex, although we tried.

02:15.670 --> 02:18.673
She's in the hospital right now,
but not because she tried to kill herself.

02:19.090 --> 02:21.888
Someone just ran me off the road
on my way home.

02:21.970 --> 02:24.211
Random? Maybe. Who knows?

02:24.310 --> 02:27.473
I can't explain any of it to you
because I don't understand it myself.

02:27.890 --> 02:30.393
Now, does knowing all this
make this any better or worse for you?

02:30.850 --> 02:33.512
Our agreement was
that we'd talk about these things.

02:34.020 --> 02:35.066
When the house is on fire,

02:35.150 --> 02:37.983
do you discuss the fire
or get out of the goddamn house?

02:39.950 --> 02:40.769
Oh.

02:42.950 --> 02:44.406
I need a fucking car.

02:50.080 --> 02:51.786
[Jessica]
I don't blame Hannah for anything.

02:54.670 --> 02:56.240
That's how it is for girls.

02:56.920 --> 03:01.209
People judge you by the way you look,
the things they hear about you.

03:05.510 --> 03:06.966
They put a label on you.

03:18.480 --> 03:21.313
I just feel like boys
get to define themselves.

03:23.700 --> 03:27.238
They get to choose their identity,
and they can hide behind it.

03:30.790 --> 03:32.200
Well, most boys.

03:34.500 --> 03:36.741
I think some know what it's like
to be afraid...

03:40.170 --> 03:43.082
to feel like the world gave you
a certain label

03:43.180 --> 03:45.546
that you have to live with
for the rest of your life.

03:46.430 --> 03:50.924
But most boys don't know what it's like.
Every single girl does.

03:51.230 --> 03:52.379
[Mrs. Davis] Your hair.

03:54.190 --> 03:57.353
You always tell me how much you like it
when it's straight.

03:59.280 --> 04:02.352
Oh, Jess, you are beautiful either way.

04:06.240 --> 04:09.073
Honey, I know this is all
very frightening,

04:09.990 --> 04:12.902
but you'll do right by Hannah
as long as you tell the truth.

04:13.620 --> 04:17.124
-You are not on trial, don't forget that.
-Yeah, Mom, I know.

04:23.760 --> 04:26.718
[Jessica] Even boys who mean well
want to tell you who you are.

04:29.180 --> 04:29.999
Hi.

04:34.730 --> 04:35.549
Hi.

04:36.310 --> 04:39.814
I, uh, I saw your mom
heading for the cafeteria,

04:39.900 --> 04:42.027
so I took my chances.

04:46.280 --> 04:50.023
-I told her it wasn't your fault.
-Isn't it a little bit my fault?

04:50.540 --> 04:51.359
No.

04:54.460 --> 04:56.200
I brought you flowers.

04:57.380 --> 04:59.666
Which now seems, uh, like, a little wrong?

04:59.750 --> 05:01.741
I don't know. Maybe I should've gotten you
a stuffed thing.

05:01.840 --> 05:03.660
This place has a stellar gift shop.

05:04.800 --> 05:06.006
What happened to your face?

05:06.880 --> 05:09.007
Uh, stupid bike thing.

05:09.100 --> 05:13.139
I tried to cut through some trees
in the dark. It doesn't matter.

05:16.560 --> 05:17.390
You matter.

05:20.940 --> 05:21.975
Are you okay?

05:23.740 --> 05:26.948
[sighs] My mom just freaked out.
It was not serious.

05:29.160 --> 05:29.979
It was surgery.

05:30.070 --> 05:32.903
It was stitches, mostly.

05:34.950 --> 05:38.954
-We had a deal.
-It was a stupid deal.

05:40.590 --> 05:42.581
You told me cutting didn't mean
you wanted to die.

05:42.670 --> 05:46.549
I don't wanna die.
I told you that and you don't understand.

05:47.470 --> 05:49.426
-Then help me.
-I can't.

05:50.260 --> 05:52.000
Because I don't understand it either.

05:55.270 --> 05:58.979
It's like I have all of these feelings,
and I can't control them,

05:59.940 --> 06:03.182
like I'm a visitor in my own mind.

06:04.230 --> 06:06.892
And if I don't catch my breath,
I'll burn up and blow away.

06:07.610 --> 06:12.980
And I know you wanna save me from that,
and I love you for it, but you can't.

06:14.240 --> 06:15.537
Then what can I do?

06:15.620 --> 06:20.569
You can figure out your own shit,
and I will figure out mine. Apart.

06:21.830 --> 06:23.582
Wait, you're-- you're breaking up with me?

06:26.130 --> 06:27.165
I'm sorry.

06:29.380 --> 06:30.335
I love you.

06:30.890 --> 06:33.597
I know. That's...

06:34.970 --> 06:36.847
[sighs] That's why I'm telling you to go.

06:39.480 --> 06:42.768
-This isn't fair.
-We have to be done, Clay. I'm sorry.

06:55.030 --> 06:57.157
I'm not just going to disappear
from your life.

06:57.500 --> 06:58.649
You already do.

07:00.870 --> 07:03.623
You-- You think about Hannah,
and you disappear.

07:05.550 --> 07:07.256
So just do it for real this time.

07:26.940 --> 07:30.103
[Jessica] So we just start expecting them
to put a label on us.

07:31.860 --> 07:33.566
_ -DykeI
[laughter]

07:35.830 --> 07:37.070
Hey, gay girl!

07:37.740 --> 07:38.570
Gross!

07:38.740 --> 07:40.196
-Lesbo!
-Lesbian!

07:43.120 --> 07:44.997
[Jessica] And we just do it to ourselves.

07:45.080 --> 07:46.536
[indistinct chattering]

07:55.510 --> 07:56.920
Welcome to the team.

07:57.180 --> 07:58.966
Don't start with me, Ryan.

07:59.060 --> 08:00.550
Hey, it happens when you're ready.

08:01.230 --> 08:03.471
I came out when I was five.
I didn't really have a choice.

08:03.770 --> 08:04.976
Guess I was just born fabulous.

08:07.020 --> 08:11.684
-I'm just glad you made it out.
-Yeah. Me, too.

08:13.200 --> 08:16.613
If you start driving a Subaru and wearing
flannel, I will hold an intervention.

08:16.700 --> 08:17.735
Be warned.

08:24.540 --> 08:27.338
-Holy shit, Alex.
-Yeah.

08:27.840 --> 08:29.740
[sighs] Who's doing this?

08:42.430 --> 08:45.763
-Hey, can you tell whose handwriting?
-Jesus, put it down.

08:45.850 --> 08:47.147
Sorry. I just...

08:48.980 --> 08:53.599
-I'm really sorry, Alex.
-So you're not alone in this.

08:54.200 --> 08:57.658
Sorry I said that.
That was really shitty, I'm just--

08:58.450 --> 09:02.284
-[sighs] This is just a lot.
-I get it. I know.

09:04.410 --> 09:05.399
Wait, your hair is different.

09:06.830 --> 09:08.991
-It's court hair.
-I don't like it.

09:09.750 --> 09:11.297
[scoffs] Noted.

09:13.300 --> 09:14.540
What the hell happened to your face?

09:17.800 --> 09:19.756
Someone ran me off the road last night.

09:20.970 --> 09:23.677
Someone in what looked
like a black Range Rover.

09:24.390 --> 09:26.472
-Bryce.
-You're not testifying.

09:27.140 --> 09:29.552
-Does he know that?
-I don't think it matters.

09:29.650 --> 09:31.470
Whoever it is,
they're coming after all of us.

09:32.360 --> 09:34.316
This came in the mail for me yesterday.

09:38.450 --> 09:40.406
-[Clay] Jesus.
-This is nuts.

09:41.530 --> 09:43.942
-We have to fucking stop him.
-How?

09:44.660 --> 09:47.868
I'm a cripple and you'll get grounded
for life if you even speak to him.

09:48.330 --> 09:50.207
Yeah, I promised my mom
I'd stay away from him.

09:50.290 --> 09:52.747
But if he's coming after me,
then what can I do?

09:54.880 --> 09:56.461
[laughs]

09:57.300 --> 09:59.177
-[Bryce] What up?
-[Scott] What's up, guys?

10:01.050 --> 10:02.176
Are we even sure it's him?

10:02.260 --> 10:04.342
[Monty] Your boy keeps looking
at you, Zach.

10:04.430 --> 10:06.671
-Does he need his diaper changed?
-Shut up, Monty.

10:06.770 --> 10:08.726
Why don't you go take care of him?
Dempsey,

10:08.810 --> 10:10.801
it's normal for nurses
to fall for their patients.

10:11.020 --> 10:13.068
[Zach] Fuck off.
I don't even like him, okay?

10:13.150 --> 10:16.642
Right. It's just your mom who makes
you carry his books and wipe his ass.

10:16.740 --> 10:18.810
-[laughter]
-No, the ass he does for pleasure.

10:24.580 --> 10:25.569
What if it's Zach?

10:26.950 --> 10:29.532
That's crazy.
He's been helping you with everything.

10:30.000 --> 10:31.627
Then why's he still hanging around Bryce?

10:31.710 --> 10:33.337
[Clay]
It's Bryce or someone protecting him.

10:34.250 --> 10:36.002
He doesn't want the truth to come out.

10:41.340 --> 10:44.093
-Why are you guys both looking at me?
-Um...

10:45.010 --> 10:47.387
Mostly 'cause you're sitting
across the table from us?

10:47.480 --> 10:49.471
You can tell them what happened to you
in court.

10:49.560 --> 10:52.438
Hannah's lawyers told me I'm just supposed
to talk about the Hot or Not List

10:52.520 --> 10:53.646
and how it ended our friendship.

10:53.770 --> 10:56.648
But you know that's not true
or it's not all that's true.

10:56.730 --> 10:59.392
-And they know it.
-But it's not part of the case.

10:59.490 --> 11:01.446
If you say it, it'll make it
part of the case.

11:01.530 --> 11:02.736
So I just say it?

11:03.240 --> 11:04.070
Jess, I--

11:05.530 --> 11:09.239
Listen. I know it's not easy, okay?

11:09.330 --> 11:11.821
Like, in no fucking universe
do I think that, but...

11:13.540 --> 11:16.623
If you tell the truth when they ask you
about your friendship,

11:16.710 --> 11:19.759
if you tell them the real reason
you stopped speaking to Hannah,

11:19.840 --> 11:21.330
then the truth is out.

11:21.430 --> 11:24.638
And this shit stops.
And Bryce gets what's coming to him.

11:25.930 --> 11:28.763
-I gotta get to first.
-Jess--

11:28.850 --> 11:31.512
You know, the truth doesn't
always make things right.

11:32.270 --> 11:34.056
You should know that better than anyone.

11:41.490 --> 11:44.482
Look, I need to remember what happened.

11:44.570 --> 11:46.731
I need the tapes.
You have to stop protecting me.

11:47.030 --> 11:50.534
-Slqe's in the hospital.
-What? What happened?

11:53.290 --> 11:54.370
I stopped protecting her.

11:56.250 --> 12:00.209
Okay, fine. Then do this for me.
Get me a ride to court today.

12:00.840 --> 12:01.829
-Alex--
-Clay.

12:06.720 --> 12:11.339
Jessica! Wow.
Oh, my God, you look amazing.

12:12.020 --> 12:14.147
-I love your hair.
-Yeah, thanks.

12:14.230 --> 12:18.724
Oh, that's right, you have court today.
Good luck, you'll be great.

12:20.230 --> 12:23.563
-Listen, about yesterday--
-It's fine. We're good.

12:23.650 --> 12:27.654
Cool. 'Cause we girls have to be strong
together, you know? Own our own shit.

12:29.240 --> 12:32.368
-I'm sorry if--
-No, no, no, right. I get it.

12:32.460 --> 12:35.418
Okay. Well, we'll miss you
at practice today.

12:35.500 --> 12:37.411
-Yeah. Thanks.
-Good luck!

12:37.670 --> 12:40.798
[Jessica] Sometimes it seems like
no matter what you do...

12:40.880 --> 12:42.962
[indistinct chattering]

12:43.050 --> 12:44.256
[silence]

12:46.890 --> 12:48.130
What's going on?

12:50.060 --> 12:52.517
[Jessica] ...people still see you
the way they want to.

13:01.320 --> 13:02.139
Who did this?

13:19.750 --> 13:20.626
Hey, are you okay?

13:20.710 --> 13:24.714
What? Why are you following me?
Just leave me alone.

13:31.560 --> 13:32.629
You think she'll talk?

13:33.720 --> 13:35.426
-Why would she?
-Why did you?

13:38.150 --> 13:40.186
Don't you get tired of hiding, Marcus?

13:41.610 --> 13:44.397
-Don't you wanna tell the truth sometimes?
-There's more than one truth.

13:46.200 --> 13:47.815
No, I don't think there is.

13:56.160 --> 13:59.209
-More press today.
-You know, you can talk to them.

13:59.670 --> 14:00.568
I don't think so.

14:00.670 --> 14:03.298
The longer you wait,
the harder it is to reclaim the narrative.

14:03.380 --> 14:05.837
-It's not my style, Jackie.
-You can make it your style.

14:06.220 --> 14:08.927
You speak for Hannah now,
and thousands of girls like her.

14:09.970 --> 14:12.848
Jessica Davis will show up for Hannah.
She's a good kid.

14:12.930 --> 14:16.514
And she's been very open
about the culture of sexism at the school.

14:17.430 --> 14:19.227
Most importantly, she's Hannah's friend.

14:23.570 --> 14:25.891
[Jessica]
But even when things get really tough...

14:27.280 --> 14:28.269
[bangs]

14:36.620 --> 14:39.828
...all it takes is just one friend
to get you through it.

14:39.920 --> 14:40.955
[Cyrus] Asshole.

14:42.790 --> 14:43.620
Hey.

14:43.710 --> 14:46.338
[Jessica]
If you're luclq, you find more than one.

14:46.420 --> 14:48.627
Toby, Eric, Chad, this is Tyler,

14:48.970 --> 14:52.428
my fellow ASS-class colleague
and extreme outcast.

14:52.680 --> 14:53.886
-What up?
-Hey, Tyler.

14:53.970 --> 14:57.519
-Yo.
-You shoot film? Super retro.

14:58.020 --> 14:59.009
Yeah. Uh...

15:00.560 --> 15:04.473
I don't know. There's something to holding
a picture, like feeling it, I don't know.

15:05.230 --> 15:07.687
Yeah. No, like, um, flipping
through a photo album

15:07.780 --> 15:09.236
instead of swiping on your phone.

15:10.400 --> 15:12.618
-Yeah, exactly.
-[chuckles]

15:12.700 --> 15:15.328
-Uh, I'm Tyler.
-Oh, I know. Mackenzie.

15:15.830 --> 15:16.899
Quiet, freaks.

15:25.630 --> 15:27.951
[Jessica] You find friends
who see through the labels.

15:31.880 --> 15:33.381
[Tony] I got it, I got it, I got it.

15:33.470 --> 15:36.257
-Thanks for the ride, Tony.
-Oh, I'm coming in with you guys.

15:37.810 --> 15:39.971
But you're on the witness list.
They check it.

15:40.060 --> 15:41.436
No, I got my brother's ID.

15:43.810 --> 15:45.266
I haven't slept in two nights.

15:45.360 --> 15:47.316
I just wanna know
what I'm looking at in there.

15:47.780 --> 15:49.395
What if you're on the list?

15:49.490 --> 15:52.311
I'll just wave my cane and cry.
It works everywhere.

15:54.660 --> 15:56.525
Wait. I bet there's
a handicapped entrance.

15:56.620 --> 15:58.326
Don't think you're supposed to say
"handicapped."

15:58.410 --> 16:00.116
-Take my arm.
-Fuck you both.

16:02.750 --> 16:04.240
[Jessica] I found those friends.

16:06.790 --> 16:08.917
That list just messed up everything.

16:09.300 --> 16:12.838
[Dennis] And was this list typical
of your experience at Liberty?

16:12.930 --> 16:14.124
Yes.

16:14.300 --> 16:18.213
Hannah was already labeled a slut.
That list just made everything worse.

16:18.310 --> 16:19.959
The truth didn't matter.

16:20.060 --> 16:21.925
That's just what they do to girls
at our school.

16:22.690 --> 16:24.760
I mean, I found these...

16:26.560 --> 16:28.187
just this morning, in my math class--

16:28.270 --> 16:30.431
Objection, these photos were not admitted
into evidence--

16:30.530 --> 16:32.896
They take one photo and it defines you,

16:33.150 --> 16:35.732
and then it becomes your job
to prove everyone wrong.

16:36.070 --> 16:38.903
This is what they did to Hannah,
and now they're doing it to me!

16:38.990 --> 16:39.820
[gavel banging]

16:39.910 --> 16:41.286
[judge] Order! Order!

16:47.460 --> 16:49.030
I can't believe he let them in.

16:50.050 --> 16:53.167
Well, they're inflammatory,
but they're relevant.

16:54.550 --> 16:55.369
Dennis.

16:57.470 --> 17:00.928
She's the girl on tape nine.
Ask her. I know she is.

17:01.020 --> 17:03.306
I can't ask her that, Olivia.
It's not relevant.

17:03.390 --> 17:04.687
It's as relevant as the pictures.

17:04.770 --> 17:07.933
It shows how the boys treated the girls
at that school,

17:08.020 --> 17:09.931
and that the school knew about it.

17:10.020 --> 17:13.433
But it didn't happen at school.
And Bryce isn't on trial.

17:19.580 --> 17:21.821
[judge] All right,
both parties will allow these photos,

17:22.290 --> 17:27.705
now Plaintiff's Exhibit 12, into evidence.

17:27.790 --> 17:31.374
-Ms. Struhl.
-Miss Davis, did you report these photos?

17:32.250 --> 17:33.706
-No.
-So you're telling me

17:33.800 --> 17:36.712
that you expect the school
to take action to protect you,

17:36.800 --> 17:38.256
but you don't tell them when an incident

17:38.340 --> 17:40.251
they're supposed
to protect you from even occurs?

17:41.180 --> 17:43.637
IfI felt like I could trust the school,
maybe I would have.

17:44.600 --> 17:49.606
Maybe Hannah would have. Oh, that's right.
She did, and look what happened.

17:50.610 --> 17:51.929
Move to strike as non-responsive.

17:52.400 --> 17:55.358
The jury will disregard
the witness's last answer.

17:55.780 --> 17:58.692
Miss Davis,
did you report the Hot or Not List?

17:59.450 --> 18:00.439
-No._
-Because, In fact,

18:00.530 --> 18:02.657
it wasn't the list _ _
that broke up your friendship, was It?

18:02.740 --> 18:03.570
It was.

18:05.160 --> 18:08.038
Do you know who put your name
and Hannah's name on the list?

18:08.790 --> 18:10.576
-Yes.
-Who?

18:14.880 --> 18:15.790
Alex Standall.

18:16.550 --> 18:18.757
And isn't it true that Alex Standall
was your boyfriend

18:18.840 --> 18:20.637
and that Hannah was jealous of that?

18:20.720 --> 18:25.419
No. We were all friends... at first.

18:26.850 --> 18:30.229
For a while, if you saw one of us,
you saw all three of us.

18:30.310 --> 18:33.518
If you're waiting for, like, the perfect
moment to choreograph your first kiss,

18:33.610 --> 18:34.929
you're gonna die a virgin.

18:35.400 --> 18:39.689
-I just want it to be special.
-Your standards are way too high.

18:39.780 --> 18:41.316
You need to lower them
like the rest of us.

18:41.410 --> 18:42.229
[Jessica chuckles]

18:42.320 --> 18:46.438
Okay, wait.
Never have I ever never been kissed.

18:46.540 --> 18:49.282
-Too soon. Too soon.
-DrInk, Hannah.

18:49.370 --> 18:51.668
-It's Sprite.
-It's fake Sprite.

18:51.750 --> 18:54.799
-It's Twist Up, actually.
-Your mom is so cheap.

18:54.880 --> 18:57.917
-That's so rude!
-What the fuck kind of name is Twist Up?

18:58.010 --> 18:59.375
When did this become a game?

18:59.550 --> 19:03.919
Okay. Never have I ever kissed
my best friend.

19:05.720 --> 19:08.348
And I don't really like
this generic shit, so...

19:08.430 --> 19:10.432
[pop music plays softly on radio]

19:13.860 --> 19:15.976
I love you anyway

19:16.110 --> 19:17.475
[chuckling]

19:19.110 --> 19:21.271
Well, uh, we're all best friends.

19:21.360 --> 19:23.567
-[Jessica laughs]
- I love you anyway

19:25.990 --> 19:27.366
[girls kiss]

19:30.080 --> 19:30.956
[chuckles]

19:34.670 --> 19:36.797
[laughter]

19:38.630 --> 19:42.179
Wouldn't you love a love life?

19:42.470 --> 19:46.099
Wouldn't you love a love life?

19:46.350 --> 19:52.220
Wouldn't you love a love life?

20:01.700 --> 20:03.770
[Jessica]
Our relationship started heating up.

20:03.860 --> 20:05.316
-I swear...
-Oh, shit.

20:05.950 --> 20:09.238
-What are you doing, crazy?
-I thought she was off Wednesdays.

20:10.870 --> 20:12.826
